Head.
Entirely yellow to yellowish-brown, only maxillary palp brown. Antenna slender and yellow to pale brown, last antennomere darker; length of second to third antennomere 0.55–0.60 (mean: 0.58), and length of third to fourth antennomere 0.83–0.86 (mean: 0.85) (
Fig. 137, 139
). Eyes large (
Fig. 137
), width of eye to interocular distance 0.55–0.61 (mean: 0.58).
